message:
sitainga = সিটাইঙ্গা, just like sit = সিট। Don't impose bengali phonology in Chittagonian. Chittagonian has its own phonology. 
Moreover, in terminological terms the 'স' in Bengali is pronounced as 'S'. Ex: Islam = ইসলাম 

According to most linguists Chittagonian deserves to be a separate language, so Sitainga would have pronounced with স while writing with Bengali script.
sitainga = সিটাইঙ্গা, just like sit = সিট। Don't impose bengali phonology in Chittagonian. Chittagonian has its own phonology.
Corrected spelling according to native pronunciation.
/* Spoken forms mainly */Fixed typo, added content
